A 22-year-old woman is one of the youngest people in Britain to be charged with assisting suicide after the death of her friend.

Milly Caller from Great Hale, Sleaford, was arrested in connection with the death of 21-year-old Emma Crossman, whose body was found in the flat she shared with her boyfriend in January. 

At the time of her death, Miss Crossman's boyfriend- who asked not to be named - claimed it may have been inspired by a Coronation Street plot. 

